-- WELLNESS & LIFESTYLE (6 resources)
('Mindful Eating Practices', 'Transform your relationship with food through awareness.', 'Eat without distractions, chew thoroughly, put utensils down between bites, notice hunger/fullness cues, appreciate food appearance and aroma, eat slowly, recognize emotional vs physical hunger. Benefits: better digestion, reduced overeating, more enjoyment.', 'article', 'wellness', ARRAY['mindful eating', 'mindfulness', 'awareness', 'habits'], true, 0),

('Creating Sustainable Healthy Habits', 'Small changes that lead to lasting transformation.', 'Start small, stack habits, track progress, focus on systems not goals, prepare for obstacles, celebrate wins, be patient with setbacks. Habit formation takes 2-3 months. Focus on one habit at a time. Environment matters - make healthy choices easy.', 'article', 'wellness', ARRAY['habits', 'behavior change', 'goals', 'motivation'], true, 0),

('Exercise and Nutrition Synergy', 'Maximize results by combining movement and nutrition.', 'Exercise increases metabolism, builds muscle, improves insulin sensitivity. Nutrition fuels workouts and recovery. Together: better body composition, energy, mood, disease prevention. Time meals around training. Combine strength training with adequate protein.', 'article', 'exercise', ARRAY['exercise', 'fitness', 'nutrition timing', 'performance'], true, 0),

('Gut-Brain Connection: Nutrition for Mental Health', 'How diet impacts mood, anxiety, and cognitive function.', 'The gut produces 90% of serotonin. Eat: omega-3s (fish), fermented foods (yogurt, kimchi), fiber (vegetables, whole grains), tryptophan (turkey, eggs). Limit sugar and processed foods. Stay hydrated. Regular meals stabilize mood. Consider probiotics.', 'article', 'wellness', ARRAY['gut-brain axis', 'mental health', 'mood', 'brain health'], true, 0),

('Dining Out: Making Healthy Choices', 'Navigate restaurant menus without stress.', 'Preview menus online, ask for modifications, start with salad or soup, choose grilled/baked over fried, request dressing/sauce on side, share dessert, avoid all-you-can-eat, eat slowly, stop when satisfied. Enjoy social experience without derailing goals.', 'article', 'wellness', ARRAY['dining out', 'restaurants', 'social eating', 'meal planning'], true, 0),

('Seasonal Eating: Benefits and Guidelines', 'Align your diet with nature''s rhythms.', 'Seasonal produce: fresher, more nutritious, better taste, lower cost, environmental benefits. Spring: asparagus, peas, strawberries. Summer: tomatoes, corn, berries. Fall: squash, apples, pears. Winter: root vegetables, citrus, dark leafy greens. Shop farmers markets.', 'article', 'nutrition', ARRAY['seasonal eating', 'local food', 'sustainability', 'produce'], true, 0);

